---
/*
  On-brand teaching diagram for /wipe-a-server ("break the RAID first").
  Top: a hardware RAID array presents member disks as ONE logical volume, so you
  get one certificate and the per-disk spare areas stay unreachable. Bottom: in
  HBA / pass-through mode each physical disk appears on its own, so each is
  sanitized and certified individually. Site palette + sans font; responsive.
*/
---

<figure class="not-prose my-8">
  <svg
    viewBox="0 0 760 386"
    role="img"
    aria-label="Two ways a server's drives are presented. In hardware RAID mode the controller exposes the member disks as a single logical volume, producing one certificate for the array and leaving each disk's spare areas unreachable. In HBA or pass-through mode each physical disk is presented individually, so each drive is sanitized and gets its own certificate."
    class="mx-auto block h-auto w-full max-w-3xl rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-2"
    style="font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;"
  >
    <title>Hardware RAID shows one logical volume and one certificate; HBA / pass-through gives a certificate per disk</title>

    <!-- ===== TOP: hardware RAID ===== -->
    <text x="24" y="34" font-size="16" font-weight="700" fill="#141922">Hardware RAID</text>
    <text x="24" y="54" font-size="12.5" fill="#5A6472">Member disks appear as one logical volume</text>

    <!-- disks -->
    <g>
      <rect x="24" y="70" width="42" height="82" rx="6" fill="#F4F6F9" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.4" />
      <rect x="72" y="70" width="42" height="82" rx="6" fill="#F4F6F9" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.4" />
      <rect x="120" y="70" width="42" height="82" rx="6" fill="#F4F6F9" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.4" />
      <rect x="168" y="70" width="42" height="82" rx="6" fill="#F4F6F9" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.4" />
    </g>
    <path d="M218 103 l16 8 l-16 8 z" fill="#3E7BFA" />
    <!-- controller -->
    <rect x="242" y="86" width="96" height="52" rx="8" fill="#EAF1FF" stroke="#3E7BFA" stroke-width="1.5" />
    <text x="290" y="109" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#1E56E6">RAID</text>
    <text x="290" y="125" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#1E56E6">controller</text>
    <path d="M346 103 l16 8 l-16 8 z" fill="#3E7BFA" />
    <!-- one logical volume -->
    <rect x="372" y="80" width="120" height="64" rx="8" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.5" />
    <text x="432" y="106" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="#141922">One logical</text>
    <text x="432" y="122" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="#141922">volume</text>
    <path d="M500 103 l16 8 l-16 8 z" fill="#98A1B0" />
    <!-- one certificate -->
    <rect x="528" y="82" width="50" height="60" rx="5" fill="#F4F6F9" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.4" />
    <line x1="538" y1="96" x2="568" y2="96" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.3" />
    <line x1="538" y1="106" x2="568" y2="106" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.3" />
    <line x1="538" y1="116" x2="558" y2="116" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.3" />
    <text x="600" y="102" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="#141922">1 certificate</text>
    <text x="600" y="120" font-size="11" fill="#B42318">spare areas unreachable</text>

    <!-- divider -->
    <line x1="24" y1="184" x2="736" y2="184" stroke="#E4E8EE" stroke-width="1.5" />

    <!-- ===== BOTTOM: HBA / pass-through ===== -->
    <text x="24" y="216" font-size="16" font-weight="700" fill="#141922">HBA / pass-through</text>
    <text x="24" y="236" font-size="12.5" fill="#5A6472">Each physical disk is presented on its own</text>

    <g>
      <rect x="24" y="252" width="42" height="82" rx="6" fill="#EAF1FF" stroke="#3E7BFA" stroke-width="1.4" />
      <rect x="72" y="252" width="42" height="82" rx="6" fill="#EAF1FF" stroke="#3E7BFA" stroke-width="1.4" />
      <rect x="120" y="252" width="42" height="82" rx="6" fill="#EAF1FF" stroke="#3E7BFA" stroke-width="1.4" />
      <rect x="168" y="252" width="42" height="82" rx="6" fill="#EAF1FF" stroke="#3E7BFA" stroke-width="1.4" />
    </g>
    <path d="M218 285 l16 8 l-16 8 z" fill="#3E7BFA" />
    <text x="244" y="289" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="#141922">Each disk</text>
    <text x="244" y="305" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="#141922">sanitized</text>
    <path d="M338 285 l16 8 l-16 8 z" fill="#3E7BFA" />

    <!-- a certificate per drive -->
    <g>
      <rect x="366" y="266" width="40" height="52" rx="5" fill="#F4F6F9" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.3" />
      <rect x="414" y="266" width="40" height="52" rx="5" fill="#F4F6F9" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.3" />
      <rect x="462" y="266" width="40" height="52" rx="5" fill="#F4F6F9" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.3" />
      <rect x="510" y="266" width="40" height="52" rx="5" fill="#F4F6F9" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.3" />
    </g>
    <circle cx="550" cy="316" r="11" fill="#158048" />
    <path d="M544.5 316 l4 4 l6.5 -8" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
    <text x="576" y="286" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="#141922">A certificate</text>
    <text x="576" y="303" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="#141922">per drive</text>
    <text x="576" y="320" font-size="11" fill="#158048">each verified</text>
  </svg>
  <figcaption class="mt-3 text-center text-sm text-muted">
    Break the RAID to HBA or pass-through mode so each physical disk is sanitized and certified on
    its own.
  </figcaption>
</figure>
